Postpartum Recovery 🌸

Postpartum recovery has been one of the hardest things I’ve ever gone through. My body is healing from the intensity of childbirth, my hormones are all over the place, and the exhaustion from sleepless nights hits hard. On top of that, I’m trying to care for a newborn while also figuring out how to care for myself. Having the right essentials right after childbirth has made a huge difference—smallest things like a Peri bottle, postpartum sanitary ice pads and even just the pain relieving spray was a life saver so were the disposable underwear’s. A good water bottle being the most important. They’ve brought comfort when I needed it most and reminded me that taking care of myself is just as important then and even now.

Details of the products used ⬇️
Peri bottle - @fridamom 
Disposable underwear- @fridamom 
Ice maxi pads - @fridamom 
Tucks Cooling pads 
Perineal foam - @fridamom 
Dermoplast Pain relieving spray
